@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Triom" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at
least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a shape and while holding the mousebutton, move
the mousepointer until it gets to the other desired shape, then,
release the mousebutton (in a drag and drop manner).

  You can move the shapes in two ways:

 -@{b}By swapping 2 shapes in a trio@{ub}: click on one shape which is located
  at either end of the choosen trio (one that is not linked with the
  other trios) and release the mousebutton on one that is in the
  center of the same trio (the shape that is linked with the other
  trios) or vise-versa.

 -@{b}By moving the linked shapes from one trio to the other@{ub}: to do this,
  click on one of the linked shapes and release the mousebutton on
  an other linked shape. This will move all the linked shapes by one
  position in the direction of the second choosen shape. Note that
  the choosen shapes must be linked next to each other.

  ...Anyway, the game will check if a move is permitted and if it
is, Triom will move the shapes accordingly.

  Try to complete each of the game boards in the least amount of
moves.

  Have fun!

